<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec124-CrossProduct" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The Cross Product</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      The big question in this section is <alert>how to approximate the area under the curve of a function</alert>. 
      We will learn some methods to approximate the area and also how to make the approximation more and more precise. 
    </p>

    <objectives>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          After this section, students will be able to:
        </p>
      </introduction>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            define what a vector is in the plane
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            perform vector addition and scalar multiplication geometrically and component-wise
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
    
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-CrossProduct">
    <title>The Cross Product</title>
    
    <figure xml:id="fig-cross-product-rhr">
      <caption>The Right Hand Rule for Cross Products</caption>
      <image source="RightHandRule_CrossProduct.png" width="50%">
          <description>A diagram showing the right hand rule where the index finger points along vector A, middle finger along B, and thumb illustrates the resulting cross product.</description>
      </image>
    </figure>

  </subsection>

</section>